@node Install "Installation"
                                 @{b}Installation@{ub}
                                ==============
note > install 040 instead of 020 should be ok 4 most cpu'es

1. run or double click eInstaller.
                       ---------- 
2. click eInstaller button on top change button type from [?] to [O]n.

3. click on Get .Config disk icon.

4. select .config file which suits your cpu (example: MpegRip040.config)

5. Install To > select your HardDisk Disk/Drawer (example: Work:Graphics/)

6. click on go arrow button.  thats all dude.

by hand - > not realy needed while you have eInstaller does everything 4 you.
-------
Copy  MpegRip0/20/40 Folder to Where ever You Want But Keep  all the files, 
In Same Drawer.   
 
eInstaller v1 can be found at www.webmem.net/portacall/
             
@endnode




@node usage "usage"

@{b}MpegRip@{ub} v1 (68k)  beta   
----------         
-Rips/Splits Mpeg Video/mp1/mp2/mp3 Files (Portacall PUI body works) 
-TestPlay (Plays Ripped Mpg video only files on window)                                 @{b}Usage@{ub}
-FunkyReq (short Prompt Window) anyone can freely use this small tool.     

-TestPlayFPU in the MpegRip drawer rename to TestPlay if you have FPU

USAGE
-----

1.run MpegRipfix/MpegRip 

->to rip video/audio files from mpeg files.
  >load a mpeg file by clicking on disk icon.
   >click on rip button [O]n
    >select video/audio by clicking cycle button
     >output not needed but unless you are ripping from cdrom
      >then click on go button.

OutPut
------
Only if you want to output ripped file to another place in harddisk or
if you dont use Output option ripped file will be in same disk/drawer.


riped output file names should get -r just before .mpg ex-> outname-r.mpg

->to split mp1/2/3/mpg video files
  >load filename in 
   >set split to [O]n
    >select video/audio by clicking cycle button
     >use up/down buttons to set number of splits you want.
       >then click go button

Output
------
Splited file will be in same drawer so output is disabled.


Frame ->sorry folks this function is removed to be used by my another app.
-----
->pos can be on with rip/split options
 >from=start file offset/frame number 
  >to end file offset/frame number

@{b}testplay@{ub} (Play button)
----------------------
-after you have riped mpeg video file you can play useing play button.
-i must say not 100% mpeg player but fairly plays.
-also you can use testplay as alone commandline testplay filename.mpg
-uses best colour correction from wb
-window play only.

unlink
------
-to cee screen shoots use commandline unlink shoots.lnk 
 ?>added new> just click UnlinkShoots
  
                              ==============


@endnode

@node Bug "Bug"
@{b}MpegRip@{ub} v1 (68k)  beta   
----------         

 @{b}Bugs@{ub} found after last compile & will be fixed on next verson.
------------------------------------------------------------
1-gui just found out gui refresh needs rework, 
(?) not fixed yet but after i get my amigaone i will use new 
    os 4.0 frontlook. anyway if you get wrong clicks close & rerun the tool.

2-if you get (Testplay not found message) try MpegRipfix or run MpegRip useing shell.
 -try no spaces in filenames for TestPlay (ex: ram disk:1.mpg ) use ram:1.mpg.

3-testplay may crash if you use wrong or not riped mpeg files (only riped .mpg files)
(?)sorry there no id checking MpegRip has so i did not bothered..

4-if you get crash playing just after riped .mpg file (try split that & retry to play)
(?)hopefully you wont get that.


Frame2Frame > skip this removed from MpegRip
------------
MPEG_FRAME_SEEK returns wrong  frame number


5- TestPlay Displays THE END / Unespected End
   on only splited mpeg video files i think. 


7-you may get Riping->Failed wrong ERROR CODE check output for result.
7-(?) bad audio file but video ok.

8-Progress bar can do funny things(i need new & better interface).

9-if more please let as fix them by you sending your bug reports at www.webmem.net

!note
MpegRip/testplay
some mixmatch function/structs are borrowed from mpeg2enc & mpeg2dec for 
TestPlay/MPegRip & they can be found at www.mpeg.org.


